td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to get a port.</span><hr size=1> As a wizard this is the one biggest thing that upsets me. <br>
<br>
<br>
DO NOT ask for a TL and then not have a clue where you want a TL to.<br>
<br>
(Portie)/tell  Could I get a TL<br>
(Me)/invite person<br>
(Me)/g Where do you need to go<br>
(Portie)/g Umm, I don't know.  Anywhere I guess.<br>
<br>
<br>
Where the @#%$ is Anywhere.   People have been lucky that I have been nice to re-ask the question for a proper reponse so far.  But those days are numbered.   <br>
<br>
For cryin out loud know where you want to go or I am going to just send you to Tox or Iceclad just to get a rid of ya.<br>
<br>
<br>
Also, is there anyone else that still hasn't figured out there are no TL's to EJ or SF?   (I am sure there are but I one can dream.) <br>
<br>
<br>
/agree on the point &quot;Don't expect a port just because he/she is a wizard.<br>
<br>
It is not our job to port people.  We do have other things to do other then port people.  Just an FYI.  <br>
<br>
Thanks for listening <p><font color="#EE1332">
